TITLE: Error Handling with Try-Catch
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to handle initial connection errors using async/await with try-catch blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/connections.md#2025-04-14_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
try {
  await mongoose.connect('mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/test');
} catch (error) {
  handleError(error);
}
```

