TITLE: Creating TimeSeries Collections in Mongoose
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the 'timeseries' option to create a TimeSeries collection in MongoDB. This is useful for efficiently storing and querying time-based data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/guide.md#2025-04-14_snippet_37

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const schema = Schema({ name: String, timestamp: Date, metadata: Object }, {
  timeseries: {
    timeField: 'timestamp',
    metaField: 'metadata',
    granularity: 'hours'
  },
  autoCreate: false,
  expireAfterSeconds: 86400
});

// `Test` collection will be a timeseries collection
const Test = db.model('Test', schema);
```

