TITLE: Defining Indexes in Mongoose Schema
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define indexes in Mongoose schemas at both path level and schema level. Shows index configuration options and auto-index settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/guide.md#2025-04-14_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const animalSchema = new Schema({
  name: String,
  type: String,
  tags: { type: [String], index: true } // path level
});

animalSchema.index({ name: 1, type: -1 }); // schema level
```

