TITLE: Avoiding Duplicate Query Execution in Mongoose
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates a common pitfall that leads to duplicate query execution in Mongoose, caused by mixing callbacks and promises with queries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/faq.md#2025-04-14_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const BlogPost = mongoose.model('BlogPost', new Schema({
  title: String,
  tags: [String]
}));

// Because there's both `await` **and** a callback, this `updateOne()` executes twice
// and thus pushes the same string into `tags` twice.
const update = { $push: { tags: ['javascript'] } };
await BlogPost.updateOne({ title: 'Introduction to Promises' }, update, (err, res) => {
  console.log(res);
});
```

