TITLE: Defining a Blog Schema in Mongoose
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define a schema structure for a blog document with various data types including String, Date, Boolean, and nested objects for metadata.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/guide.md#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import mongoose from 'mongoose';
const { Schema } = mongoose;

const blogSchema = new Schema({
  title: String, // String is shorthand for {type: String}
  author: String,
  body: String,
  comments: [{ body: String, date: Date }],
  date: { type: Date, default: Date.now },
  hidden: Boolean,
  meta: {
    votes: Number,
    favs: Number
  }
});
```

