TITLE: Compiling a Mongoose Model from Schema
DESCRIPTION: Creates a Mongoose model named 'Tank' from a schema with name and size properties. Mongoose automatically looks for the plural, lowercased version of the model name in the database.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/models.md#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const schema = new mongoose.Schema({ name: String, size: String });
const Tank = mongoose.model('Tank', schema);
```

