TITLE: Domain Socket URI Encoding in Mongoose 5.x
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to properly encode domain sockets in MongoDB connection strings for Mongoose 5.x, which is required due to more stringent URI parsing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/migrating_to_5.md#2025-04-14_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Works in mongoose 4. Does **not** work in mongoose 5 because of more
// stringent URI parsing.
const host = '/tmp/mongodb-27017.sock';
mongoose.createConnection(`mongodb://aaron:psw@${host}/fake`);

// Do this instead
const host = encodeURIComponent('/tmp/mongodb-27017.sock');
mongoose.createConnection(`mongodb://aaron:psw@${host}/fake`);
```

