TITLE: HydratedDocument Type Changes - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the changes in HydratedDocument type parameters between Mongoose 6 and 7, showing both old and new implementations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/docs/migrating_to_7.md#2025-04-14_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type HydratedDocument<
  DocType,
  TMethodsAndOverrides = {},
  TVirtuals = {}
> = Document<unknown, any, DocType> &
Require_id<DocType> &
TMethodsAndOverrides &
TVirtuals;
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type HydratedDocument<
  DocType,
  TOverrides = {},
  TQueryHelpers = {}
> = Document<unknown, TQueryHelpers, DocType> &
Require_id<DocType> &
TOverrides;
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Mongoose 6 version:
type UserDocument = HydratedDocument<TUser, TUserMethods, TUserVirtuals>;

// Mongoose 7:
type UserDocument = HydratedDocument<TUser, TUserMethods & TUserVirtuals, TUserQueryHelpers>;
```

