TITLE: Advanced Mongoose Schema with Validators and Middleware
DESCRIPTION: Example of a more complex Mongoose Schema with custom validators, setters, and middleware.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Automattic/mongoose/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-14_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const Comment = new Schema({
  name: { type: String, default: 'hahaha' },
  age: { type: Number, min: 18, index: true },
  bio: { type: String, match: /[a-z]/ },
  date: { type: Date, default: Date.now },
  buff: Buffer
});

// a setter
Comment.path('name').set(function(v) {
  return capitalize(v);
});

// middleware
Comment.pre('save', function(next) {
  notify(this.get('email'));
  next();
});
```

